The chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Former Governors Forum and former Yobe State governor, Senator Bukar Abba Ibrahim, has congratulated the new national officers of APC headed by Senator Abdulahi Adamu. Ibrahim said the new members of the National Working Committee (NWC) of APC are coming on board at a critical time in the history of the party and Nigeria, especially with the party primaries coming up soon nationwide. A statement jointly signed by the former Yobe State governor and High Chief Sunnie Chukumele, chairman and publicity secretary of the Forum respectively, said, “The experience many of the members of the Executives will be very useful in navigating the most active political period before 2023. As a group of stakeholders in the party, APC Former Governors Forum look forward to working with the new Executives. “While wishing the chairman and other members of the Executives success, the Forum of APC Former Governors enjoin APC members nationwide to cooperate with Sen. Abdulahi Adamu and other members of the Executives,” the statement stated.